In JavaScript you can do this:

### Regex version

```js
const s = "col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-7 col-xxl-6 p-3 p-md-4 p-lg-5";

const result = (s.match(/col(?:-[a-z]+)?-\d+/g) || []).join(" ");

console.log(result);
```

**Output:**

```
col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-7 col-xxl-6
```

---

### Split + Filter version

```js
const s = "col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-7 col-xxl-6 p-3 p-md-4 p-lg-5";

const result = s.split(" ").filter(c =&gt; c.startsWith("col-")).join(" ");

console.log(result);
```

**Output:**

```
col-12 col-md-10 col-lg-7 col-xxl-6
```

